// Content Sprint 7: Product and Catalogue Management.
window.CONTENT_SPRINT_7 = {"product-model":{"summary":"Understand how Marketplacer structures Seller products as Adverts and Variants, how Categories and Prototypes determine available attributes, and how identifiers, pricing, stock, shipping and wholesale settings work together.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller onboarding","Ecommerce and technology","Commercial teams"],"sections":{"Understanding the Product Model":"\n<p>Marketplacer represents a Seller product through an <strong>Advert</strong> and one or more <strong>Variants</strong>.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Advert</strong><p>The shared product information, such as title, description, Brand, Category and product images.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Variant</strong><p>The purchasable version, with its own SKU, barcode, price, stock, shipping and Variant Option Values.</p></div></div></div>\n<p>A customer purchases a Variant rather than the Advert itself. The selected Variant becomes a Line Item on the relevant Seller Invoice.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use Marketplacer terminology consistently.</strong> Teams may casually say product, listing or item, but platform configuration and troubleshooting are clearer when Advert, Variant and Line Item are used precisely.</div>\n","Advert and Variant Relationship":"\n<p>Information common to every purchasable version belongs at Advert level. Information that can differ by version belongs at Variant level.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Advert-level examples</th><th>Variant-level examples</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Product name, Brand, Category, description, features and shared images</td><td>SKU, barcode, price, sale price, stock and Shipping Profile</td></tr><tr><td>Advert Option Values such as material or product type</td><td>Variant Option Values such as size, colour or capacity</td></tr><tr><td>Product publication intent</td><td>Variant publication, availability and commercial model</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Changing the Advert updates the shared product definition. Changing one Variant affects only that purchasable version unless an integration or bulk process deliberately updates several Variants.</p>\n","Single and Multi-Variant Products":"\n<p>A single-Variant product has one purchasable version. A multi-Variant product groups several valid combinations under one Advert.</p>\n<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Single Variant</h3><p>One mug, one book edition or one service package. The product still requires a Variant because price, stock and fulfilment belong at Variant level.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Multiple Variants</h3><p>A shirt offered in several sizes and colours, or a device offered in several capacities.</p></article></div>\n<p>Each Variant should represent a real purchasable combination. Avoid creating duplicate combinations, placeholder Variants or combinations that the Seller cannot fulfil.</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Define the Variant model before Seller onboarding.</strong> The Category Prototype and Variant Option Types should support the way customers select the product on the storefront.</div>\n","Identifiers and Matching":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Identifier</th><th>Use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Advert ID</td><td>Marketplacer identifier for the Seller Advert</td></tr><tr><td>Variant ID</td><td>Marketplacer identifier for the specific purchasable Variant</td></tr><tr><td>SKU</td><td>Seller-controlled operational identifier used for stock, fulfilment and reconciliation</td></tr><tr><td>Barcode</td><td>GTIN, UPC or EAN identifier where applicable, used for validation and product matching</td></tr><tr><td>External ID</td><td>Reference to the connected source product or another approved system</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Retain Advert IDs and Variant IDs when updating existing records. Removing them from an update workflow can create duplicates instead of changing the intended product.</p>\n<p>Barcodes should follow the applicable GTIN format and check-digit rules. SKUs should remain stable and unique within the agreed marketplace policy.</p>\n","Product Content and Images":"\n<p>Titles, descriptions, features, specifications and images should help customers identify the product and make an informed decision.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Use a clear title without Seller-store promotions or unnecessary keyword repetition</li><li>Provide an accurate description and required compliance information</li><li>Use a clear primary image and relevant alternate images</li><li>Use Variant images where the visible Variant differs</li><li>Add meaningful image alt text where required</li></ul>\n<p>In spreadsheet workflows, images are supplied as publicly accessible URLs rather than embedded files. Image 1 is the primary image, followed by the supported alternate image columns.</p>\n","Pricing, Stock, Shipping and Wholesale":"\n<p>Every sellable Variant needs commercially and operationally valid information.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Base Price</td><td>Standard customer selling price</td></tr><tr><td>Sale Price</td><td>Temporary customer selling price where configured</td></tr><tr><td>Stock</td><td>Available quantity or the approved infinite-stock setting</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping Profile</td><td>Connects the Variant to Marketplacer Shipping Rules where used</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale Price</td><td>Starting amount owed to the Seller for a wholesale Variant</td></tr><tr><td>RRP</td><td>Reference retail price where used</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Wholesale is configured per Variant.</strong> Each applicable Variant must have <strong>Variant is wholesale</strong> selected and a positive Wholesale Price. Entering a Wholesale Price alone does not change the pricing model.</div>\n","Categories, Prototypes and Attributes":"\n<p>The selected Category determines the Prototype and therefore the Advert and Variant attributes available for the product.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Select the most appropriate Category</strong><p>Use the marketplace taxonomy rather than a broad fallback Category.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Apply the Category Prototype</strong><p>The Prototype exposes the approved Advert and Variant Option Types.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Complete required attributes</strong><p>Use approved Option Values so products can be filtered and validated consistently.</p></div></div></div>\n<p>An incorrect Category can cause the wrong attributes and Catalog Rules to apply. Complete Mapping before evaluating Category-specific validation failures.</p>\n","Create Products through Bulk Product Management":"\n<p>For Bulk Product Management product creation, the spreadsheet requires Product name, Brand, Base price, Main description, at least one Image and Stock level. The selected Category and its Prototype determine the additional Advert and Variant attributes that appear.</p>\n<p>The row marked <span class=\"code-pill\">new</span> creates the Advert and its first Variant. Use additional <span class=\"code-pill\">variant</span> rows only for the second and subsequent Variants. A single-Variant product ordinarily uses only the <span class=\"code-pill\">new</span> row.</p>\n<p>Marketplacer generates the Advert ID and Variant ID after successful upload. Preserve those identifiers when managing the product later.</p>\n","Validate Product Structure":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Advert contains information shared by every Variant</li><li>Every Variant is a real purchasable combination</li><li>SKU and barcode policy is met</li><li>Category, Brand and Option Values are approved</li><li>Price, stock and Shipping Profile are valid</li><li>Wholesale Variants are marked correctly and contain a positive Wholesale Price</li><li>Product and Variant images match the actual offer</li><li>Catalog Rules pass and Product Vetting is completed where enabled</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8332949936397-Bulk-Product-Management-Overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bulk Product Management Overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/10611212114957-View-or-edit-a-product-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View or Edit a Product in the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39486294561293-Bulk-upload-spreadsheet-reference\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bulk Upload Spreadsheet Reference</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["categories","Categories"],["prototypes","Prototypes"],["option-types","Option Types"],["bulk-product-management","Bulk Product Management"],["product-source-of-truth","Product Source of Truth"]]},"product-ingestion":{"summary":"Determine how each Seller's existing product source will connect to Marketplacer, select the most appropriate ingestion method and define how products, prices, inventory and future changes will be maintained.","audience":["Seller onboarding","Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Technology and integrations","Sellers"],"sections":{"Choose an Ingestion Method for Each Seller":"\n<p>Seller product sources vary by Seller. One Seller may already maintain its catalogue in Shopify, BigCommerce or another ecommerce platform. Another may manage products in a spreadsheet, ERP or PIM. Another may prefer to connect through the Seller API or an approved integration partner.</p>\n<p>Confirm the product source and ongoing update method separately for every Seller rather than applying one ingestion method across the marketplace.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller example</th><th>Product source</th><th>Possible method</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller A</td><td>Shopify</td><td>MConnect</td></tr><tr><td>Seller B</td><td>Spreadsheet</td><td>Bulk Product Management</td></tr><tr><td>Seller C</td><td>ERP or PIM</td><td>Seller API</td></tr><tr><td>Seller D</td><td>Small catalogue</td><td>Seller Portal</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","Seller Portal":"\n<p>Use manual Seller Portal entry for small catalogues, controlled testing and Sellers that do not maintain a suitable source file or integration.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Seller creates the Advert and first Variant</li><li>Seller selects Category, Brand and attributes</li><li>Seller enters price, stock, shipping and identifiers</li><li>Seller publishes or submits for Product Vetting</li></ul>\n<p>Manual entry is easy to begin but can become time-consuming for larger catalogues. Agree who will maintain future changes before launch.</p>\n","Bulk Product Management":"\n<p>Use Bulk Product Management when the Seller can maintain structured spreadsheet data or when a controlled bulk correction is required.</p>\n<p>The Seller can add new products or manage existing product information, using either a Single Sheet or Multi Sheet workbook. The current generated workbook should be used for every task so columns, Categories, Brands and Option Values reflect the marketplace configuration.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>This is the current spreadsheet experience.</strong> Older references to the Legacy Bulk Product Uploader or V1 relate to a retired workflow.</div>\n","MConnect":"\n<p>MConnect connects supported Seller ecommerce platforms to Marketplacer. It can import products and continue synchronising selected fields such as description, images, price and stock.</p>\n<p>Confirm the connector, product-selection rules, mapping ownership, publication approach and ongoing fields to synchronise before the full import.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Source-platform changes can replace Marketplacer edits.</strong> Correct synchronised fields in the Seller platform or deliberately remove that field from ongoing MConnect synchronisation.</div>\n","Seller API and Integration Partners":"\n<p>Use the Seller GraphQL API or an approved integration partner when the Seller maintains products in an ERP, PIM, custom commerce platform or another system that requires a tailored connection.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Define create and update ownership</li><li>Retain Advert and Variant IDs</li><li>Use stable external identifiers and safe retry logic</li><li>Capture validation errors and Catalog Rule failures</li><li>Monitor integration health and provide a manual fallback</li></ul>\n<p>A hybrid model can be designed where one source creates the catalogue and another updates a specific field, but every field needs one authoritative write path.</p>\n","XML and Product Feeds":"\n<p>XML or another supported product-feed workflow may suit Sellers that already publish a structured catalogue feed.</p>\n<p>Confirm retrieval schedule, authentication, source identifiers, image accessibility, Category and attribute mapping, failed-row handling and inactive-product behaviour.</p>\n<p>Feed schedules and supported behaviour differ from MConnect. Test the exact connector rather than assuming all integrations process updates in the same way.</p>\n","Operator-Assisted and Hybrid Models":"\n<p>Operator-assisted onboarding can help a Seller prepare an initial file, complete Mapping or correct a controlled launch sample. It should not create permanent ambiguity over who maintains the catalogue.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Hybrid example</th><th>Required control</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Shopify creates products, Seller Portal assigns Shipping Profiles</td><td>Shipping Profile remains Marketplacer-specific</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect creates catalogue, ERP updates stock through API</td><td>Stock removed from ongoing MConnect sync and ERP updates existing Variant IDs</td></tr><tr><td>Seller supplies offers, Golden Products supply central content</td><td>Backfill policy and field ownership documented</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","Select, Test and Govern the Method":"\n<p>Evaluate product volume, update frequency, Seller capability, source data quality, integration effort, launch timing and long-term operating cost.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Product source confirmed</li><li>Initial creation method confirmed</li><li>Ongoing update method confirmed</li><li>Pricing, stock and image ownership documented</li><li>Mapping owner assigned</li><li>Product Vetting and Catalog Rules tested</li><li>Failure monitoring and fallback process agreed</li><li>Representative products validated on the storefront</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8332949936397-Bulk-Product-Management-Overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bulk Product Management Overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003175271-Shopify-integration-for-sellers-Configure-Shopify\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Shopify Integration for Sellers</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003175331-Sync-products-via-XML\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sync Products via XML</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller API Documentation</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["product-model","Product Model"],["bulk-product-management","Bulk Product Management"],["mconnect","MConnect"],["mapping","Mapping"],["product-source-of-truth","Product Source of Truth"]]},"bulk-product-management":{"summary":"Help Sellers create, update and troubleshoot Adverts and Variants through the current Bulk Product Management workflows, while Operators maintain the marketplace structures and controls that shape each workbook.","audience":["Sellers","Seller onboarding","Catalogue teams","Marketplace operations","Support teams"],"sections":{"Understanding Bulk Product Management":"\n<p>Bulk Product Management is the Seller Portal workflow for creating and maintaining many Adverts and Variants through spreadsheets.</p>\n<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Add new products</h3><p>Create products and Variants in selected Categories, including Categories the Seller does not yet offer and Categories already represented in their catalogue.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Manage product information</h3><p>Update or enrich the current catalogue and, where needed, add new products or Variants within Categories already represented in that catalogue.</p></article></div>\n<p>Both functions offer <strong>Single Sheet</strong> and <strong>Multi Sheet</strong> workbooks in the current Production and Sandbox experience.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>This page covers Bulk Product Management V2.</strong> Older references to the Legacy Bulk Product Uploader or V1 relate to a retired workflow.</div>\n","Operator and Seller Responsibilities":"\n<p>Bulk Product Management is primarily a <strong>Seller workflow</strong>. Sellers generate, edit and upload their own workbooks from the Seller Portal.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller responsibility</th><th>Operator responsibility</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Select the correct workflow and workbook format</td><td>Configure the marketplace Categories, Brands and product structure</td></tr><tr><td>Enter accurate product, Variant, price, stock, image and shipping data</td><td>Maintain Prototypes, Option Types, Option Values and Shipping Profiles</td></tr><tr><td>Preserve identifiers when updating existing records</td><td>Define Catalog Rules, Mapping and Product Vetting requirements</td></tr><tr><td>Review upload results and correct failed rows</td><td>Help resolve configuration gaps and explain marketplace standards</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Support the Seller without becoming the permanent data-entry team.</strong> Operators may assist with the first upload, but the ongoing source, ownership and maintenance process should be agreed during Seller onboarding.</div>\n","Choose Add New or Manage Product Information":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Workflow</th><th>Best used for</th><th>Spreadsheet source</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Add new products</strong></td><td>Initial catalogue setup, launching into a new Category, or adding fresh products to a selected existing Category</td><td>Built from the Categories selected when generating the workbook</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Manage product information</strong></td><td>Updating or enriching the existing catalogue, recategorising products, and adding products or Variants in Categories already represented in the catalogue</td><td>Generated from the Seller's current catalogue</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Download and upload through the same function. An <strong>Add new products</strong> workbook must be uploaded through Add new products. A <strong>Manage product information</strong> workbook must be uploaded through Manage product information.</p>\n<p>Manage product information is not limited to edits. Sellers can also enter <span class=\"code-pill\">new</span> and <span class=\"code-pill\">variant</span> in the <strong>Ad ID</strong> column to create products and Variants within the relevant existing Categories.</p>\n","Generate a Current Workbook":"\n<p>In the Seller Portal, go to <code>Products &gt; Bulk Manage Products</code>, then choose the workflow that matches the task.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Select the workflow</strong><p>Choose Add new products or Manage product information.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Choose Single Sheet or Multi Sheet</strong><p>Select the workbook structure that best supports the work.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Select the required fields</strong><p>Include all mandatory fields and any optional fields needed for the change.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Generate the workbook</strong><p>Download a current file rather than reusing an old permanent template.</p></div></div></div>\n<p>For Add new products, select one or more Categories to generate Category-specific fields, or leave the Category selection blank to generate a broader workbook and choose Categories within the file.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Mandatory fields are bold and marked with a red asterisk</li><li>Keep the original headers and worksheet names</li><li>Do not unlock, rename or edit system lookup sheets</li><li>Generate a fresh workbook after Category, Brand, Prototype or Option Value changes</li><li>Back up the Seller's source file before making a large update</li></ul>\n","Understand the Workbook Sheets":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Workbook area</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Usage Guide</strong></td><td>Instructions for creating, updating and clearing product data. Treat this as the first reference for the generated file.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>All Products</strong></td><td>The main working sheet in a Single Sheet workbook.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Category sheets</strong></td><td>One working sheet per Category in a Multi Sheet workbook, with Category-specific columns and guided values.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Missing Category</strong></td><td>Used in applicable Multi Sheet workflows to assign Brand and Category before richer Category-specific editing.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Data</strong></td><td>Locked reference information used by validations and dropdowns. Do not edit this sheet.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>The exact sheets depend on the selected workflow, format and catalogue. Always follow the Usage Guide included in the workbook that was just generated.</p>\n","Choose Single Sheet or Multi Sheet":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Format</th><th>Best for</th><th>Guided fields</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Single Sheet</strong></td><td>Fast, wide changes across many products using filters, formulas or macros</td><td>Category and Brand dropdowns. Option and attribute columns are present but do not have dropdowns.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Multi Sheet</strong></td><td>Category-by-Category work, richer product setup and guided attribute entry</td><td>Dropdowns for Brands, Shipping Profiles and supported Category-specific Option Types and Option Values</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Single Sheet places the selected catalogue in one <strong>All Products</strong> worksheet. Multi Sheet separates the work into Category-specific sheets.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Enter Single Sheet option values exactly.</strong> Because option and attribute columns do not have dropdowns, Sellers must use the exact marketplace-supported value shown in the Data sheet or supplied by the Operator.</div>\n","Add Products and Variants":"\n<p>Use the exact lowercase keywords in the <strong>Ad ID</strong> column:</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Enter <span class=\"code-pill\">new</span></strong><p>This row creates the Advert and its first purchasable Variant.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Add <span class=\"code-pill\">variant</span> rows underneath</strong><p>Use one row for each second or subsequent Variant belonging to that Advert.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Leave generated IDs blank</strong><p>Marketplacer creates the Ad ID and Variant ID after a successful upload.</p></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong><span class=\"code-pill\">new</span> and <span class=\"code-pill\">variant</span> are case-sensitive.</strong> Enter them exactly as shown in the Ad ID column. Do not enter them in Variant ID or another system field.</div>\n<p>A single-Variant product normally uses only the <span class=\"code-pill\">new</span> row because that row already creates the first Variant.</p>\n<p>Required creation fields typically include Product name, Brand, Base price, Main description, at least one Image and Stock level. The selected Category and Prototype determine additional required Advert and Variant attributes.</p>\n","Update Existing Products and Clear Values":"\n<p>Generate a Manage product information workbook from the current Seller catalogue and retain the existing <strong>Ad ID</strong> and <strong>Variant ID</strong> values.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Edit only the fields intended for the upload</li><li>Do not change Category numbers, generated IDs or other system-controlled values</li><li>Keep product and Variant rows grouped correctly</li><li>Review formulas before replacing them with final values</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Blank does not mean delete.</strong> In Manage product information, an empty cell is ignored and leaves the existing value unchanged.</div>\n<p>To clear a supported optional field, enter:</p><p><span class=\"code-pill\">DELETE_VALUE</span></p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li><span class=\"code-pill\">DELETE_VALUE</span> is case-sensitive</li><li>Use it only for optional fields that support clearing</li><li>Do not use it in mandatory or system fields</li><li>Confirm the result after upload because the previous value is not restored automatically</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Protect identifiers.</strong> Removing or altering Ad ID or Variant ID can prevent the intended update or create an unintended duplicate.</div>\n","Resolve Missing Categories":"\n<p>In a Multi Sheet Manage product information workbook, uncategorised products can appear in the <strong>Missing Category</strong> sheet.</p>\n<ol><li>Open the Missing Category sheet.</li><li>Assign the required <strong>Brand</strong>.</li><li>Assign the correct <strong>Category</strong>.</li><li>Save and upload the workbook through Manage product information.</li><li>Generate a fresh Manage product information workbook.</li><li>Locate the product in its new Category sheet.</li><li>Complete the Category-specific attributes and upload again.</li></ol>\n<p>The first upload establishes the Category. The fresh workbook then exposes the correct Prototype-driven option columns for the second stage of editing.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Fix marketplace configuration first when the correct choice is unavailable.</strong> The Operator may need to add or correct the Brand, Category, Prototype, Option Type or Option Value before the Seller regenerates the workbook.</div>\n","Images and Multi-Select Values":"\n<h3>Images</h3><p>Supply publicly accessible image URLs rather than embedded images or spreadsheet thumbnails. Image 1 is the primary image, followed by the supported alternate-image columns.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Use the full externally accessible image URL</li><li>Confirm the link opens without requiring a login</li><li>Do not use thumbnail URLs</li><li>Use product and Variant images that accurately represent the item</li><li>Google Drive and Dropbox links are supported when the generated link resolves correctly</li></ul>\n<h3>Multi-select values</h3><p>Where a field accepts several approved values, separate them with a pipe:</p><p><span class=\"code-pill\">Value one | Value two</span></p>\n<p>Each value must already be accepted by the relevant Option Type. A correctly placed pipe does not make an unsupported value valid.</p>\n","Wholesale Fields Where Enabled":"\n<p>Where wholesale is enabled and the generated workbook exposes the relevant fields, Sellers can create or update the wholesale configuration at Variant level.</p>\n<p>Available columns can depend on the marketplace configuration and selected fields. They may include Pricing Model, Wholesale Price, Variant Wholesale Price, Recommended Retail Price and Variant Recommended Retail Price.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Set every applicable Variant to the wholesale pricing model</li><li>Enter a positive Variant Wholesale Price</li><li>Complete RRP fields where required</li><li>Retain Ad IDs and Variant IDs for updates</li><li>Review representative Variants after upload</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Wholesale Price alone does not activate wholesale.</strong> Every applicable Variant must be marked as wholesale.</div>\n<p>Use the dedicated <strong>Wholesale Configuration</strong> topic for the marketplace's commercial model, Seller agreement and pricing-governance decisions.</p>\n","Upload and Review Results":"\n<p>Return to the same Bulk Manage Products workflow used to generate the workbook, upload the file and review the result shown in that workflow's recent import or export history.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Result</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Response</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Successful rows</td><td>The spreadsheet rows were processed</td><td>Validate representative Adverts and Variants in Manage Products</td></tr><tr><td>Failed rows or error workbook</td><td>Some rows could not be processed</td><td>Review headers, IDs, required values, exact option values and row structure</td></tr><tr><td>Product validation errors</td><td>The record exists but does not meet marketplace requirements</td><td>Review product errors, Mapping, Catalog Rules and Product Vetting</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>A completed job can still contain failed rows. Compare the expected, successful and failed counts before treating the upload as complete.</p>\n<p>When an error workbook is returned, correct the failed rows rather than re-uploading successful rows unnecessarily.</p>\n<h3>Publication after upload</h3>\n<p><strong>Publish Advert = Yes</strong> and <strong>Publish Variant = Yes</strong> express publication intent. They do not guarantee that the offer will appear on the storefront.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Stock must be available unless infinite stock is valid</li><li>Mapping must be complete</li><li>Catalog Rules must pass</li><li>Product Vetting must be approved where enabled</li><li>The Seller and Advert must remain active</li><li>The connected storefront must receive and display the offer correctly</li></ul>\n<p>Barcode validation follows the applicable GTIN format and check-digit rules.</p>\n","Troubleshoot Common Seller Issues":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller reports</th><th>Operator should check</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Brand is unavailable</td><td>Whether the Brand exists, is approved and is available in the generated workbook</td></tr><tr><td>Product has no valid Category</td><td>Mapping, the Missing Category workflow and whether the correct Category exists</td></tr><tr><td>Required field or value is unavailable</td><td>Prototype, Option Type, Option Value and Category configuration</td></tr><tr><td>Variant is rejected</td><td>Whether each Variant has a valid and unique Option Value combination</td></tr><tr><td>A value did not clear</td><td>Whether the Seller left the cell blank instead of using <span class=\"code-pill\">DELETE_VALUE</span></td></tr><tr><td>The wrong record changed or a duplicate appeared</td><td>Whether Ad ID, Variant ID or another system field was altered</td></tr><tr><td>Upload completed but some products did not change</td><td>Successful and failed row counts and any returned error workbook</td></tr><tr><td>Product uploaded but is not live</td><td>Publish fields, stock, Mapping, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting, Seller status and storefront synchronisation</td></tr><tr><td>Manual edits are later overwritten</td><td>Whether MConnect, API or another source still owns and synchronises that field</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Correct the source of truth.</strong> Do not keep repairing a field in Marketplacer when an active integration will overwrite it from the Seller's source system.</div>\n","Operational Controls":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Use a workbook generated for the current Seller, workflow and environment</li><li>Keep an untouched backup of the downloaded file</li><li>Test a small representative group before a large catalogue change</li><li>Avoid overlapping MConnect, API or spreadsheet updates to the same fields</li><li>Protect Ad IDs, Variant IDs and system columns</li><li>Review failed rows before retrying</li><li>Validate Category, Brand, Variant structure, price, stock and Shipping Profile</li><li>Validate wholesale status where enabled</li><li>Confirm Mapping, Catalog Rules and Product Vetting</li><li>Check representative products in the Seller Portal and on the storefront</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Define a safe bulk-change process.</strong> Agree who prepares, reviews, uploads, validates and, where necessary, rolls back significant catalogue changes.</div>\n","Video Walkthroughs and Related Articles":"\n<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Adding New Products</h3><p>Walkthrough of creating new products through Bulk Product Management.</p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1KGDVqdHmTmbN1cFNJRVW4ZNd0_0vub5h/view?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Watch the video</a></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Updating Existing Products</h3><p>Walkthrough of managing existing product information.</p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1UW0r13g-HB_5Q558RK2Au6LdWuuIJNiH/view?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Watch the video</a></article></div>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39486165269645-Bulk-product-management-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bulk Product Management Overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/32368677868813-How-to-add-products-and-variants-into-categories-in-bulk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to Add Products and Variants into Categories in Bulk</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/34159145753869-How-to-manage-products-and-variants-in-bulk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to Manage Products and Variants in Bulk, Multi Sheet</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41580919800077-How-to-manage-products-and-variants-in-bulk-single-sheet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to Manage Products and Variants in Bulk, Single Sheet</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39486294561293-Bulk-upload-spreadsheet-reference\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bulk Upload Spreadsheet Reference</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["product-model","Product Model"],["product-ingestion","Product Ingestion Methods"],["mapping","Mapping"],["catalog-rules","Catalog Rules"],["wholesale-configuration","Wholesale Configuration"]]},"mconnect":{"summary":"Connect supported Seller ecommerce platforms to Marketplacer, configure product, Order and inventory behaviour, understand the MConnect workspace and monitor source-to-Marketplacer synchronisation.","audience":["Sellers","Seller onboarding","Marketplace operations","Technology and integrations","Catalogue teams"],"sections":{"Understanding MConnect":"\n<p>MConnect imports products from a supported Seller ecommerce platform and can continue synchronising selected product fields. It can also support Order export and inventory updates according to the connector and configured settings.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Seller source platform</strong><p>Products, prices, stock and other Seller-owned data are maintained.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>MConnect</strong><p>Retrieves, transforms and sends supported data.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Marketplacer</strong><p>Applies Mapping, validation, Product Vetting and publication controls.</p></div></div></div>\n<p>Most connected Sellers continue maintaining synchronised product information in their ecommerce platform and use the Seller Portal for Marketplacer-specific activities.</p>\n","Connect the Seller Platform":"\n<p>Use the setup guide for the Seller's source platform:</p>\n<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Shopify</h3><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003175271-Shopify-integration-for-sellers-Configure-Shopify\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open setup guide</a></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>WooCommerce</h3><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360035231951-Connect-and-set-up-WooCommerce-integration\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open setup guide</a></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Maropost Commerce</h3><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360034856532-Maropost-Commerce-Cloud-Connection-Setup\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open setup guide</a></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>BigCommerce</h3><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039602272-BigCommerce-integration-setup-for-Marketplacer-sellers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open setup guide</a></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Adobe Commerce</h3><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360045090431-Adobe-Commerce-Magento-2-integration-for-sellers-Set-up-connection\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open setup guide</a></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>XML</h3><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003175331-Sync-products-via-XML\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open setup guide</a></article></div>\n<p>Follow the current connector-specific instructions. New Shopify connections from 1 January 2026 use Shopify's Dev Dashboard connection process.</p>\n","Use the MConnect Workspace":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Tab</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Imports</td><td>Run a manual import, process updated items and review job IDs, triggers and fetched or uploaded counts</td></tr><tr><td>Items</td><td>Search by Advert ID, Variant ID, SKU, barcode or status and inspect source, transformation and Marketplacer results</td></tr><tr><td>Invoices</td><td>Export new Seller Invoices, compare Marketplacer Invoice ID with source Order ID and review errors or cancellation status</td></tr><tr><td>Settings</td><td>Configure product, Order, inventory and account behaviour before full import and whenever the workflow changes</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>The Item detail view helps isolate whether an issue exists in the source product, MConnect transformation or Marketplacer result. Use the individual Import action for a controlled product test.</p>\n","Configure Product Import":"\n<p>Review the product source and selection controls before enabling a full import.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Product source or source collection</li><li>Tags, one per line and case-sensitive where shown</li><li>Excluded Brands</li><li>Ignore barcodes where explicitly approved</li><li>Automatically publish products</li><li>Enable product imports</li><li>Only import new products with stock</li><li>Category source</li><li>Remove links from descriptions</li><li>Golden Product barcode or SKU matching where enabled</li></ul>\n<p>Publication intent does not bypass Mapping, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting, stock or Seller-account requirements.</p>\n","Configure Ongoing Synchronisation":"\n<p>On initial creation, MConnect sends the supported product information required to create the Advert and Variants. After creation, <strong>Attributes to sync once product has been created</strong> determines which fields continue updating existing records.</p>\n<p>These can include title, description, images, price, stock, SKU, barcode and other connector-supported fields.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Manual edits can be overwritten.</strong> Where a field remains selected for synchronisation, the next source update can replace the Marketplacer value. Deselect the field only when Marketplacer is deliberately becoming its source of truth.</div>\n<h3>Image modes</h3><ul><li><strong>Disabled:</strong> ongoing image synchronisation does not run</li><li><strong>Sync and preserve:</strong> source images are updated while approved Marketplacer images can remain</li><li><strong>Sync and delete:</strong> Marketplacer images absent from the source can be removed</li></ul>\n","Configure Orders, Inventory and Account Settings":"\n<h3>Order Settings</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Sync Seller Invoices</li><li>Set the appropriate start date</li><li>Add Order tags where supported</li><li>Decide whether customer email is excluded</li></ul>\n<h3>Inventory Settings</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Stock buffer</li><li>Inventory Mapping location ID</li><li>Only import new products with stock</li><li>Never set stock to infinite where that behaviour is not intended</li></ul>\n<h3>Configuration Settings</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Currency conversion</li><li>GST configuration for applicable Australian accounts</li><li>Failed import notification email</li></ul>\n<p>Review settings after any Seller platform change, warehouse migration, fulfilment change or catalogue-source change.</p>\n","Complete Mapping and Publication":"\n<p>Imported source values may require Mapping before products can proceed.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Map Categories</li><li>Map Brands</li><li>Map Option Types</li><li>Map Option Values</li><li>Confirm Product Vetting ownership</li><li>Resolve Catalog Rule failures</li><li>Assign Shipping Profiles where Marketplacer Shipping Rules are used</li></ul>\n<p>Mapping may be completed by the Seller, the Operator, an implementation partner or Marketplacer SRM where that service is included. Confirm responsibility and turnaround during onboarding.</p>\n","Monitor and Troubleshoot":"\n<p>Use Imports, Items and Invoices to trace each workflow.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Evidence</th><th>What it helps confirm</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Import job ID and counts</td><td>Whether source products were fetched and uploaded</td></tr><tr><td>Item detail</td><td>Source value, MConnect transformation and Marketplacer result</td></tr><tr><td>Import error</td><td>Why the product could not be created or updated</td></tr><tr><td>Invoice source Order ID</td><td>Whether the Seller Invoice exported to the source platform</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect Audit Logs</td><td>Which settings changed, when and by whom</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Collect Seller, source platform, MConnect account, source product ID, Advert ID, Variant ID, job ID, timestamps, expected result, actual result and screenshots before escalation.</p>\n","Reset, Delete and Govern the Connection":"\n<p><strong>Reset Your Account</strong> clears MConnect account data so the connection can be configured again. <strong>Delete Your Account</strong> removes the connection. Existing Marketplacer Adverts remain unless separately managed.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Resetting or reconnecting can create duplicates.</strong> Review existing Marketplacer products, matching settings and source identifiers before reimporting.</div>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Product source documented</li><li>Ongoing sync fields documented</li><li>Mapping owner assigned</li><li>Shipping Profile process agreed</li><li>Image mode tested</li><li>Inactive-product behaviour tested</li><li>Order and inventory settings tested</li><li>Error monitoring assigned</li><li>Reset or deletion requires approval</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003175271-Shopify-integration-for-sellers-Configure-Shopify\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Shopify Settings and Best Practices</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/24734785464845-Golden-Records-and-MConnect\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Configurable Product Data Sync</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039602272-BigCommerce-integration-setup-for-Marketplacer-sellers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manually Import Products through MConnect</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4408171619469-MConnect-Using-Audit-Logs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MConnect: Using Audit Logs</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["product-ingestion","Product Ingestion Methods"],["mapping","Mapping"],["product-source-of-truth","Product Source of Truth"],["catalog-rules","Catalog Rules"],["integration-troubleshooting","Integration Monitoring"]]},"mapping":{"summary":"Translate Seller source Categories, Brands, Option Types and Option Values into approved marketplace values, understand the standard and AI-enabled workspaces and assign clear review ownership.","audience":["Catalogue teams","Seller onboarding","Marketplace operations","Sellers","Marketplacer SRM where included"],"sections":{"Understanding Mapping":"\n<p>Mapping translates product values from a Seller's source system into the approved Marketplacer taxonomy and attribute model.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Seller source value</strong><p>For example, source Category \"Mens Trainers\".</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Marketplace value</strong><p>For example, Footwear &gt; Men's Shoes &gt; Athletic Shoes.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Reusable mapping</strong><p>Future products with the same source value can use the confirmed destination.</p></div></div></div>\n<p>Complete Mapping before interpreting Category-specific Prototype or Catalog Rule errors.</p>\n","What the Mapping Area Looks Like":"\n<p>Open the standard workspace through:</p><p><code>Seller Portal &gt; Products &gt; Mapping</code></p>\n<p>The standard experience has four tabs:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Brand</li><li>Category</li><li>Option type</li><li>Option value</li></ul>\n<p>The number beside each tab indicates source values requiring attention. Use search, Mapped, Skipped and Exclude items with 0 products filters. Each row can show product count, suggested destinations and actions such as Skip, Edit and Confirm.</p>\n<h3>AI Product Mapping</h3><p>Where AI Product Mapping is enabled, the top-level areas are Categorisation, Brands, Option Types and Option Values. Categorisation includes AI suggestions, Categorisation required, Products categorised and Category mappings.</p>\n","Map Categories and Brands":"\n<p>Map each source Category to the most specific suitable marketplace Category. Review the affected product count before confirming a broad source mapping.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Confirm the product belongs in the destination Category</li><li>Review the Prototype and required attributes</li><li>Avoid a broad parent Category when a correct leaf exists</li><li>Check whether the source value includes several unrelated product types</li></ul>\n<p>Map source Brand values to approved Marketplacer Brands. Create or request a new Brand only after checking naming, spelling, punctuation and duplicates.</p>\n","Map Option Types and Option Values":"\n<p>Option Type Mapping aligns the Seller's source attribute name with the marketplace attribute. Option Value Mapping aligns the individual value.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Source</th><th>Marketplace</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Colour / Color / Shade</td><td>Colour</td></tr><tr><td>Navy blue / Navy</td><td>Navy</td></tr><tr><td>Adult size</td><td>Size</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Confirm whether an Option Type belongs at Advert or Variant level. Variant Option Values must create valid purchasable combinations.</p>\n","Use Automatic and AI Suggestions":"\n<p>Automatic or AI suggestions can accelerate review, but they remain recommendations until confirmed.</p>\n<p>In the AI-enabled Categorisation view, search by title, keyword, barcode or SKU, apply filters, compare the product with the suggested Category and select Confirm or Recategorise.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Control bulk actions.</strong> Review representative products and affected counts before confirming a large set of suggestions.</div>\n","Review, Confirm and Remap":"\n<p>Use Confirm when the source-to-marketplace relationship is correct. Use Skip only where the value is intentionally excluded and the resulting product behaviour is understood.</p>\n<p>Remap when taxonomy, Prototype or Seller source data changes. A Category remap can affect attributes, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting and front-end placement for every product using that source value.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Record the old and new destination</li><li>Review affected products</li><li>Validate representative Adverts</li><li>Confirm the storefront result</li><li>Communicate material changes to the Seller</li></ul>\n","Assign Mapping Ownership":"\n<p>Mapping ownership varies by marketplace and service model. It may sit with:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Your marketplace catalogue team</li><li>The Seller</li><li>An implementation partner</li><li>Marketplacer SRM where that service is included</li></ul>\n<p>Confirm the responsibility during Seller onboarding and record target turnaround, escalation and approval authority. Products should not remain unavailable while each party expects another team to complete Mapping.</p>\n","Validate and Govern Mapping":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Standard or AI-enabled workspace understood</li><li>Category, Brand, Option Type and Option Value queues reviewed</li><li>Source product counts checked before confirmation</li><li>Category Prototype and Catalog Rules validated</li><li>Variant combinations checked</li><li>Skipped values documented</li><li>Remapping change process agreed</li><li>Backlog and turnaround monitored</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039602272-BigCommerce-integration-setup-for-Marketplacer-sellers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Product Mapping Overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/19655643593101-Catalog-rules\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Catalog Rules</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/17741316387725-Review-and-approve-products-adverts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Review and Approve Products</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["categories","Categories"],["option-types","Option Types"],["mconnect","MConnect"],["product-vetting","Product Vetting"],["catalog-rules","Catalog Rules"]]},"product-source-of-truth":{"summary":"Define where each Seller's product information is created, corrected, enriched and maintained, then prevent competing updates across the Seller source, Marketplacer, Golden Products and the storefront.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller onboarding","Technology and integrations","Ecommerce teams"],"sections":{"Understanding Product Source of Truth":"\n<p>Product Source of Truth answers a practical question:</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Where should each product field be corrected so the next update preserves the approved value?</strong></div>\n<p>For most Sellers connected through MConnect, the operating model is straightforward. The Seller continues maintaining its product catalogue in Shopify or another connected ecommerce platform. Depending on the connector settings, this can include titles, descriptions, images, SKUs, barcodes, prices, inventory, availability and Variant information.</p>\n<p>The Seller may still use the Seller Portal for Marketplacer-specific activities such as assigning a Shipping Profile, completing Mapping where contractually responsible, reviewing errors and completing enrichment that is not controlled by the connected source.</p>\n<p>Mapping may be owned by the Operator, Seller, an implementation partner or Marketplacer SRM where that service is included. Confirm responsibility during onboarding.</p>\n","Define Ownership at Field Level":"\n<p>Source of truth is assigned per Seller and per field, not once for the entire marketplace.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Possible authority</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Title and description</td><td>Seller ecommerce platform, PIM or Golden Product</td></tr><tr><td>Price</td><td>Seller source, Operator pricing system or controlled Marketplacer workflow</td></tr><tr><td>Stock</td><td>Seller ecommerce platform, ERP or warehouse system</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping Profile</td><td>Marketplacer Seller Portal</td></tr><tr><td>Mapping</td><td>Marketplacer Mapping area</td></tr><tr><td>Front-end collection or SEO</td><td>Operator ecommerce platform</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Several systems may hold the same value, but one should have the approved write authority.</p>\n","Apply the Model by Ingestion Method":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Typical source model</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller Portal</td><td>Marketplacer is the main product write path</td></tr><tr><td>Bulk Product Management</td><td>Controlled workbook and Marketplacer IDs govern changes</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect</td><td>Seller ecommerce platform governs selected synchronised fields</td></tr><tr><td>Seller API</td><td>ERP, PIM or custom source governs the API payload</td></tr><tr><td>XML</td><td>Feed-generating system governs supplied fields</td></tr><tr><td>Hybrid</td><td>Ownership is split deliberately by field</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>A hybrid model can use Shopify to create and maintain the catalogue while an ERP updates inventory through the Seller API. This requires Stock to be removed from ongoing MConnect synchronisation and the ERP to update existing Variant IDs.</p>\n","Manage MConnect Synchronisation and Manual Edits":"\n<p>On initial creation, MConnect can supply the supported product fields. After creation, the selected ongoing sync fields determine what can overwrite Marketplacer.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Identify the incorrect field</strong><p>Confirm whether MConnect still synchronises it.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Correct the authoritative source</strong><p>Usually the Seller ecommerce platform for synchronised fields.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Validate the Marketplacer update</strong><p>Review MConnect Items and the resulting Advert or Variant.</p></div></div></div>\n<p>Deselect a field only when Marketplacer is deliberately becoming authoritative for that field.</p>\n<p>Review image mode and the setting that marks missing or inactive source products inactive, because these can remove images or set stock to zero.</p>\n","Separate Seller, Marketplacer and Front-End Ownership":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Layer</th><th>Typical responsibility</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller source</td><td>Product facts, price, stock, images and operational identifiers</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer</td><td>Category and attribute governance, Mapping, Shipping Profile, Product Vetting, Catalog Rules and commercial configuration</td></tr><tr><td>Operator ecommerce platform</td><td>Collections, SEO, merchandising, campaign placement, search synonyms and storefront presentation</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Document any value copied between layers and the system allowed to overwrite it.</p>\n","Handle Enrichment and Manual Exceptions":"\n<p>Marketplace-specific enrichment should be maintained directly in Marketplacer only when the connector does not control the field or that field has been deliberately removed from ongoing synchronisation. Otherwise the next source update may replace the enrichment.</p>\n<p>Use a controlled exception record for urgent manual changes:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Seller and product identifiers</li><li>Field and current source</li><li>Reason for the exception</li><li>Temporary or permanent ownership</li><li>Integration change required</li><li>Owner and review date</li></ul>\n<p>For wholesale Sellers, record the source of truth for both <strong>Variant is wholesale</strong> and Wholesale Price. A new Variant or price update that omits the wholesale pricing model can cause commission treatment instead.</p>\n","Use Golden Products as a Central Product Source":"\n<p>Golden Products can provide an Operator-managed central product definition while Seller Adverts and Variants remain the individual offers.</p>\n<p>Define whether the Golden Product controls title, description, Brand, Category, images, specifications and Golden Variant information. Seller price, inventory, shipping and fulfilment generally remain Seller-offer data.</p>\n<p>Backfill policy determines whether central data is never applied, fills only missing fields or always replaces supported Seller fields.</p>\n","Change or Migrate the Product Source":"\n<p>Treat a source migration as a controlled integration change.</p>\n<ol><li>Export and record existing Advert IDs, Variant IDs, SKUs, barcodes and external IDs.</li><li>Define the new field ownership model.</li><li>Stop or narrow the old write path.</li><li>Test representative products in Sandbox.</li><li>Connect the new source to existing records.</li><li>Validate price, stock, images, shipping and publication.</li><li>Monitor for duplicates and unexpected overwrites.</li></ol>\n<p>Do not reconnect a source as a new catalogue without reviewing existing Marketplacer records and matching behaviour.</p>\n","Govern and Monitor Product Data Ownership":"\n<p>Maintain a source register by Seller and field. Review it during onboarding, integration changes, catalogue-quality investigations and Seller handover.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Primary write path documented</li><li>Ongoing sync fields documented</li><li>Manual exceptions recorded</li><li>Wholesale status and cost ownership recorded</li><li>Mapping and Shipping Profile ownership assigned</li><li>Golden Product backfill policy recorded</li><li>Activity Logs and integration logs monitored</li><li>Storefront result validated</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003175271-Shopify-integration-for-sellers-Configure-Shopify\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Shopify Settings and Best Practices</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/24734785464845-Golden-Records-and-MConnect\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Golden Records and MConnect</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/24734837065613-Backfill-and-Autopublish\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Backfill and Autopublish</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003175331-Sync-products-via-XML\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sync Products via XML</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["product-ingestion","Product Ingestion Methods"],["mconnect","MConnect"],["bulk-product-management","Bulk Product Management"],["golden-records","Golden Records and Central Product Database"],["catalogue-quality","Catalogue Quality Operations"]]},"product-vetting":{"summary":"Review Seller Adverts before they become available to customers, configure the approval checkpoint safely, give actionable rejection feedback and monitor important changes to approved products.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller onboarding","Category managers","Compliance teams"],"sections":{"Understanding Product Vetting":"\n<p>Product Vetting is the Operator review and approval process for Seller Adverts. It provides a human quality-control checkpoint between product preparation and customer availability.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Seller creates or imports product</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Mapping and Catalog Rules complete</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Operator reviews the Advert and Variants</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Approve or reject</strong></div></div></div>\n<p>Use vetting to review Category, Brand, titles, descriptions, images, attributes, Variant combinations, Shipping Profiles, pricing, wholesale configuration and applicable compliance requirements.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Approval is not publication by itself.</strong> Stock, valid published Variants, Seller account state, shipping, downstream synchronisation and storefront indexing still affect availability.</div>\n","Decide When to Use Product Vetting":"\n<p>Product Vetting is configured per Seller. It is particularly useful for new Sellers, regulated Categories, curated catalogues, manually created products and large launch imports requiring approval.</p>\n<p>A lighter model may suit a trusted integrated Seller with consistently strong data and effective Catalog Rules.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller</th><th>Possible model</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>New Seller</td><td>All products require vetting</td></tr><tr><td>Trusted integrated Seller</td><td>Catalog Rules and approved-product change monitoring</td></tr><tr><td>Regulated Category Seller</td><td>Specialist review before publication</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Before enabling vetting broadly, assign reviewers, target turnaround, specialist escalation and bulk-approval authority.</p>\n","Configure Product Vetting Safely":"\n<p>Navigate to <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller</code> and enable <strong>Require all products to be vetted</strong>.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Review the existing catalogue first.</strong> Enabling vetting for a live Seller can take its products offline until they are reviewed and approved.</div>\n<p>Authorised Operator users need the applicable product-catalogue permission. Configure access through <code>Configuration &gt; User Roles &amp; Permissions &gt; Manage Roles &amp; Permissions</code>.</p>\n<p>Configure Catalog Rules before a large catalogue enters the queue so routine missing-field failures are identified automatically.</p>\n","Review the Product Vetting Workspace":"\n<p>Navigate to <code>Adverts &gt; Product Vetting</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Tab</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Requires vetting</td><td>Active approval queue</td></tr><tr><td>Rejected</td><td>Products returned for Seller correction</td></tr><tr><td>Recently updated</td><td>Selected changes to products already approved, where monitoring is enabled</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Search by complete Product ID, SKU or barcode, or use a partial product name. Filter by Seller, Brand, Category, stock, previous rejection and Catalog Rule status.</p>\n","Review and Approve Products":"\n<p>Review product identity, description, images, Advert attributes, Variant structure, SKU, barcode, price, stock, Shipping Profile, tax and wholesale configuration.</p>\n<p>Before editing an imported product directly, identify its source of truth. Correct a synchronised Shopify description in Shopify rather than making an Operator edit that MConnect will later replace.</p>\n<p>Select <strong>Approve &amp; Next</strong> after completing the review. Use bulk approval only for a controlled group with the same trusted Seller, Category, source pattern and validated sample.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Sample single and multi-Variant products</li><li>Review several Brands and product types</li><li>Confirm Mapping and Catalog Rules</li><li>Validate downstream publication after approval</li></ul>\n","Reject and Resubmit Products":"\n<p>Reject a product when it needs Seller correction or is unsuitable for publication. The rejection reason should identify the affected field, the problem, the expected standard and where the correction should be made.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use actionable feedback.</strong> “Replace the main image with a clear full-product image against a neutral background” is more useful than “Bad image”.</div>\n<p>The Seller can filter <strong>Rejected via vetting</strong> in <code>Products &gt; Manage Products</code>, correct the product and select <strong>Save &amp; Submit</strong>. <strong>Save &amp; Exit</strong> stores the change without resubmitting it.</p>\n<p>Where the generated workbook includes <strong>Resubmit for vetting</strong>, corrected Adverts can also be resubmitted in bulk.</p>\n","Monitor Approved Product Changes":"\n<p>Configure post-approval monitoring through <code>Configuration &gt; Product Settings &gt; Advert Settings</code> and enable <strong>Notify of advert changes</strong>. Select the product and Variant fields that should appear in the Recently updated queue.</p>\n<p>Changed values can become live before this post-publication review. Approving clears the item and retains the change. Rejecting takes the Advert offline and returns it to the Seller.</p>\n<p>Prioritise high-risk fields such as price, sale price, Category, Brand, images, SKU, barcode, Shipping Profile, tax, wholesale values and regulated-product information. Recently updated entries remain available for a limited review period, so assign a regular cadence.</p>\n","Coordinate Mapping, Catalog Rules and Source Corrections":"\n<p>Product Vetting should be the final human checkpoint rather than the first place routine data errors are found.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Product ingestion</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Mapping</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Catalog Rules</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Product Vetting</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Publication</strong></div></div></div>\n<p>Return source-owned corrections to the source. Correct Marketplacer-owned fields, such as Shipping Profile or Mapping, through the approved Marketplacer workflow.</p>\n","Govern Product Vetting Operations":"\n<p>Define a Category-based review standard, assign queue owners and monitor approval time, rejection rate, repeat rejection, backlog and recently updated items.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Vetting decision recorded per Seller</li><li>Existing-product impact assessed</li><li>Review standard and permissions configured</li><li>Mapping and Catalog Rules ready</li><li>Individual and bulk approval tested</li><li>Rejection and resubmission tested</li><li>Approved-product monitoring assigned</li><li>Wholesale Variants checked individually</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/17741291671693-Configure-product-advert-review-and-approval-vetting\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Configure Product Review and Approval</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/17741316387725-Review-and-approve-products-adverts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Review and Approve Products</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27467503428237-Reviewing-vetted-and-approved-products-and-variants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Review Changes to Vetted Products</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/17741129664141-Troubleshoot-products-adverts-rejected-by-the-operator-vetting\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Troubleshoot Rejected Products</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator User Role Permissions</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["mapping","Mapping"],["catalog-rules","Catalog Rules"],["product-source-of-truth","Product Source of Truth"],["catalogue-quality","Catalogue Quality Operations"],["seller-onboarding-process","Seller Onboarding Process"]]},"catalog-rules":{"summary":"Define automated product-data requirements that Seller Adverts and Variants must meet before Product Vetting or publication, then test, monitor and improve those rules safely.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller onboarding","Category managers","Compliance and technology"],"sections":{"Understanding Catalog Rules":"\n<p>Catalog Rules are automated validation requirements applied to Seller Adverts and Variants.</p>\n<p>Rules can require information such as descriptions, images, SKUs, barcodes, Shipping Profiles, positive prices and wholesale values.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Control</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Mapping</td><td>Translates Seller source values</td></tr><tr><td>Catalog Rules</td><td>Validate measurable product requirements</td></tr><tr><td>Product Vetting</td><td>Provides human review and approval</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Catalog Rules identify issues. They do not write or enrich the missing product content.</p>\n","Plan Your Catalog Rule Set":"\n<p>Start with launch-critical standards that can be assessed consistently.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Product title present</li><li>Description present or above an agreed length</li><li>Product image present</li><li>Variant SKU present and unique</li><li>Barcode present where required</li><li>Shipping Profile present</li><li>Variant price greater than zero</li><li>Variant Wholesale Price present for wholesale products</li></ul>\n<p>Use marketplace-wide scope for universal requirements and Category-specific scope for information such as ingredients, dimensions, compatibility or regulatory warnings.</p>\n<p>Judgement-based standards, such as image quality or persuasive copy, belong in Product Vetting or Catalogue Quality Operations.</p>\n","Create and Manage Catalog Rules":"\n<p>Navigate to <code>Adverts &gt; Catalog Rules</code> and select <strong>Create new rule</strong>.</p>\n<ol><li>Select the Attribute.</li><li>Select the supported Condition.</li><li>Enter the Value where required.</li><li>Add Categories for Category-specific scope.</li><li>Select the Rule outcome.</li><li>Write an actionable Seller error message.</li><li>Create and test the rule.</li></ol>\n<p>Rules can be enabled, disabled or deleted according to their lifecycle. Review current behaviour before changing a live Category-specific rule because some configuration changes may require recreation.</p>\n","Choose Attributes, Conditions and Values":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Question</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Attribute</td><td>What field is checked?</td></tr><tr><td>Condition</td><td>How is it assessed?</td></tr><tr><td>Value</td><td>What requirement must be met?</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Conditions can include Present, numerical comparisons, text contains or excludes, starts with, no HTML, valid formats and Unique.</p>\n<p>Use Unique cautiously for SKU and barcode after assessing historical duplicates and Seller identifier practices.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>A wholesale price rule does not activate wholesale.</strong> Each applicable Variant must also be marked as wholesale.</div>\n","Understand Validation and Rule Outcomes":"\n<p>New and offline products that fail an applicable rule can be saved but cannot progress to Product Vetting or publication until corrected.</p>\n<p>For existing online products, choose the rule outcome:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Outcome</th><th>Existing online product</th><th>New or offline product</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Warning</td><td>Remains online with an error</td><td>Cannot progress until corrected</td></tr><tr><td>Unpublish</td><td>Taken offline</td><td>Cannot progress until corrected</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Use Warning for staged remediation. Use Unpublish where missing or invalid information creates material fulfilment, legal, safety or customer risk.</p>\n","Review and Correct Catalog Rule Errors":"\n<p>Sellers can view active rules through <code>Products &gt; Marketplace Catalog Rules</code> and affected products through <code>Products &gt; Manage Products</code>.</p>\n<p>Correct the authoritative source:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Source</th><th>Correction location</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Shopify through MConnect</td><td>Shopify for synchronised fields</td></tr><tr><td>Seller API or XML</td><td>Seller source system or feed</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Portal or spreadsheet</td><td>Marketplacer through the approved workflow</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping Profile or Mapping</td><td>Marketplacer</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Operators can filter Product Vetting and Search Adverts for products with Catalog Rule errors and export invalid products for controlled correction.</p>\n","Test and Roll Out Rule Changes":"\n<p>Assess affected products, Sellers, Categories and online status before enabling a rule.</p>\n<ol><li>Test passing and failing products in Sandbox.</li><li>Include online, offline, multi-Variant and integrated products.</li><li>Test parent and child Category scope.</li><li>Confirm Warning or Unpublish behaviour.</li><li>Communicate the requirement and correction path.</li><li>Allow background processing to complete before evaluating final counts.</li></ol>\n<p>A staged approach can introduce a rule as Warning, remediate the catalogue and later change the approved future standard to Unpublish.</p>\n","Govern Catalog Rules":"\n<p>Maintain a rule register with Rule ID, Attribute, Condition, Value, scope, outcome, business purpose, owner and review date.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Review duplicate or contradictory rules</li><li>Monitor failures by Seller, Category and Attribute</li><li>Convert recurring errors into training, Mapping or source improvements</li><li>Review rules when Categories, Prototypes, shipping, wholesale or regulations change</li><li>Assign authorised rule administrators</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/19655643593101-Catalog-rules\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Catalog Rules</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/19169079466765-Create-Catalog-rules\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create Catalog Rules</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/34052081776781-How-Catalog-Rules-work\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How Catalog Rules Work</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/38201826375437-Understanding-Catalog-Rule-Conditions-for-Data-Validation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Understanding Catalog Rule Conditions</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/34049716990861-Filtering-products-with-catalog-rule-errors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Filtering Products with Catalog Rule Errors</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["product-vetting","Product Vetting"],["mapping","Mapping"],["catalogue-quality","Catalogue Quality Operations"],["product-source-of-truth","Product Source of Truth"],["prototypes","Prototypes"]]},"golden-records":{"summary":"Configure and operate the Central Product Database, maintain trusted Golden Products and Golden Variants, link equivalent Seller offers, control central content propagation and manage matching, backfill, buy-box inputs, duplicates, merges and customer-facing offer selection.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller onboarding","Ecommerce teams","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understand Golden Records":"\n<p>The <strong>Central Product Database</strong>, or <strong>CPD</strong>, is the Operator-managed catalogue containing Golden Records.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Golden Product</strong><br>Shared product identity and content</div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Golden Variants</strong><br>Specific sizes, colours, capacities or other configurations</div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Seller offers</strong><br>Separate price, stock, shipping and fulfilment records</div></div></div>\n<p>Seller Adverts and Seller Variants can link to the equivalent Golden Product and Golden Variant. This allows several Sellers offering the same real-world product to share a central product identity while continuing to maintain separate commercial offers.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Golden Record can support</th><th>What remains Seller-specific</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Shared title, description, Brand, Category, images and specifications</td><td>Seller identity, price, stock, shipping and fulfilment</td></tr><tr><td>Barcode-based matching and product enrichment</td><td>Seller SKU and Seller-owned source data</td></tr><tr><td>Consolidated product pages and buy-box experiences</td><td>The actual purchasable Line Item and Seller Invoice</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>The Golden Record does not fulfil an Order.</strong> The customer purchases a linked Seller Variant, and that Seller Variant becomes the Line Item on the Seller Invoice.</div>\n","Decide Whether Your Marketplace Needs Golden Records":"\n<p>Golden Records are valuable when several Sellers offer the same branded products and the marketplace wants a controlled central product identity.</p>\n<h3>Golden Records are a strong fit when</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Several Sellers stock the same real-world products</li><li>Reliable EAN, UPC or GTIN identifiers are available</li><li>The storefront should consolidate equivalent Seller offers</li><li>The Operator wants shared descriptions, images and specifications</li><li>Sellers should be able to list products by matching existing CPD information</li><li>A preferred-offer or buy-box experience is planned</li></ul>\n<h3>The standard Seller Advert model may be better when</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Most products are unique, handmade, personalised or one-off</li><li>Product identity cannot be established reliably</li><li>Sellers use inconsistent or reused barcodes</li><li>Each Seller offer should appear as a separate customer listing</li><li>The Operator does not have the governance capacity to maintain central records</li></ul>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Architecture decision</th><th>Questions to answer</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer experience</td><td>Will customers see one shared product page or separate Seller listings?</td></tr><tr><td>Offer selection</td><td>Can customers choose a Seller, or will the storefront select one?</td></tr><tr><td>Product identity</td><td>Which identifiers prove that two products are identical?</td></tr><tr><td>Central content</td><td>Which attributes belong to the Golden Record?</td></tr><tr><td>Seller content</td><td>Which attributes remain Seller-specific?</td></tr><tr><td>Data source</td><td>Which linked Advert can update central content?</td></tr><tr><td>Backfill</td><td>Can Golden Record content fill or overwrite Seller content?</td></tr><tr><td>Governance</td><td>Who reviews, merges, deletes and audits Golden Records?</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Enable Golden Records only when the consolidated-product use case and operating model are clear.</strong></div>\n","Understand Golden Products, Variants and Seller Offers":"\n<h3>Golden Product</h3><p>The Golden Product represents the shared product identity. It can contain the title, description, Brand, Category, images, specifications, features, measurements and other shared product metadata.</p>\n<h3>Golden Variant</h3><p>The Golden Variant represents a specific version of the product, such as a size, colour, capacity, flavour, pack size, model or configuration. Each Golden Variant can contain the barcode and Option Values that identify that version.</p>\n<h3>Seller Advert and Seller Variant</h3><p>The linked Seller record remains the purchasable offer.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Golden Record responsibility</th><th>Seller-offer responsibility</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Shared product identity</td><td>Seller identity</td></tr><tr><td>Shared title and description</td><td>Base and Sale price</td></tr><tr><td>Brand and Category</td><td>Stock</td></tr><tr><td>Shared imagery and specifications</td><td>Seller SKU</td></tr><tr><td>Golden Variant structure</td><td>Shipping Profile</td></tr><tr><td>Shared Option Values</td><td>Fulfilment and dispatch</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>The exact field ownership depends on Golden Product Settings, the selected source Advert, Seller backfill policy, MConnect settings, the connected storefront and marketplace governance.</p>\n","Plan the Customer and Offer Experience":"\n<p>Golden Records provide the central product structure, but the connected storefront determines how customers experience linked Seller offers.</p>\n<h3>One product page with one preferred offer</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Shared product content</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Storefront selects an eligible Seller offer</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Customer sees the selected price and availability</strong></div></div></div>\n<h3>One product page with several Seller offers</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller</th><th>Price</th><th>Delivery</th><th>Availability</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller A</td><td>$100</td><td>2 days</td><td>In stock</td></tr><tr><td>Seller B</td><td>$95</td><td>5 days</td><td>In stock</td></tr><tr><td>Seller C</td><td>$105</td><td>Collection available</td><td>In stock</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Before implementation, define how Golden Products and linked Seller offers are retrieved, when an offer is eligible, how unavailable offers are handled, how product URLs are managed and how customer service identifies the Seller that fulfilled the Order.</p>\n<h3>Advanced pattern: multi-market localisation</h3><p>A multi-market Operator may maintain one Golden Record for the same physical product while storing approved language-specific content in structured custom attributes. The storefront then selects the correct field for the active locale. This requires a deliberately designed product model and frontend mapping. Marketplacer does not automatically choose which translated field the storefront should display.</p>\n","Understand Buy-Box Responsibility":"\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Golden Records enable a buy-box experience. They do not provide native buy-box ranking.</strong></div>\n<p>When several Sellers are linked to the same Golden Variant, Marketplacer exposes those Seller offers and their available data. The connected storefront or orchestration layer decides:</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Which offers are eligible</li><li>Which Seller is displayed by default</li><li>Whether all offers are shown</li><li>How offers are ranked</li><li>How ties are resolved</li><li>What happens when the preferred offer becomes unavailable</li></ul>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Golden Records provide</th><th>The storefront provides</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Shared product identity</td><td>Buy-box selection</td></tr><tr><td>Golden Variant grouping</td><td>Seller ranking</td></tr><tr><td>Linked Seller offers</td><td>Preferred-offer logic</td></tr><tr><td>Product and offer relationships</td><td>Price, shipping, SLA or commercial prioritisation</td></tr><tr><td>API-accessible offer data</td><td>Customer-facing display rules</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Hidden buy box</h3><p>The storefront automatically selects one Seller offer and displays it as the main purchasable offer.</p>\n<h3>Overt buy box</h3><p>The storefront displays several Seller offers and allows the customer to compare or choose one.</p>\n<h3>Define the selection rule</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Lowest item price</li><li>Lowest landed price, including shipping</li><li>Fastest delivery</li><li>In-stock availability</li><li>Seller performance or strategic priority</li><li>Operator margin</li><li>A weighted combination of approved factors</li></ul>\n<pre><code>1. Exclude unpublished or out-of-stock offers\n2. Rank by total customer price\n3. If tied, rank by delivery speed\n4. If still tied, rank by Seller priority</code></pre>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Golden Records enable the buy box. The Operator implements the buy-box calculation.</strong></div>\n","Configure Golden Product Settings":"\n<p>Go to:</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; Product Settings &gt; Golden Product Settings</code></p>\n<p>These settings determine how Golden Records are created, linked, updated and protected.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Setting</th><th>What it controls</th><th>Operator consideration</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Automatically create Golden Product and Variant records from new Variants with unique barcodes</td><td>Creates Golden Records when an eligible Seller Variant does not match an existing Golden Variant</td><td>Can grow the CPD quickly, but relies on trusted identifiers and Seller data</td></tr><tr><td>Create new Golden Products and Variants with an active status</td><td>Creates new records as Active rather than Draft</td><td>Active supports automation; Draft supports human review</td></tr><tr><td>Automatically link matching Variants to Golden Products and Variants</td><td>Links eligible Seller Variants whose barcode matches a Golden Variant</td><td>Incorrect or reused barcodes can create incorrect relationships</td></tr><tr><td>Enforce strict barcode rules for Golden Variants</td><td>Requires one unique barcode for each Golden Variant</td><td>Improves identity integrity but may exclude products without reliable GTINs</td></tr><tr><td>Enable propagation of Seller updates to Golden Records</td><td>Allows the source Seller Advert to update Golden Record content</td><td>Gives the selected source Seller influence over central content</td></tr><tr><td>Enable Golden Record data source fallback</td><td>Selects another linked Advert when the current source is deleted</td><td>The replacement source may contain different or lower-quality content</td></tr><tr><td>Restrict barcode updates on Variants linked to Golden Variants</td><td>Prevents Sellers changing or removing linked barcodes</td><td>Protects links but requires an Operator correction process</td></tr><tr><td>Enable merging of Golden Products</td><td>Allows Golden Products sharing Variant barcodes to merge automatically</td><td>Merging is permanent and retained content is not reconciled automatically</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Automated marketplace model</h3><p>Use trusted barcodes, auto-create, Active status and auto-linking when Seller data is reliable and exceptions are monitored.</p>\n<h3>Curated marketplace model</h3><p>Use auto-create with Draft status when catalogue users need to review or enrich central records before activation.</p>\n<h3>Operator-controlled model</h3><p>Disable automatic creation and linking when the Operator creates the CPD through the UI, API or controlled bulk upload.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Test every setting in Sandbox before enabling it in Production.</strong> Several settings can create, link, overwrite, merge or protect records at scale.</div>\n","Manage Active and Draft Status":"\n<p>New Golden Products and Golden Variants can be created as <strong>Active</strong> or <strong>Draft</strong>.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>At least one Active Golden Variant</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Golden Product is Active</strong></div></div></div>\n<p>When no Golden Variant is Active, the Golden Product remains Draft.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Use Active when</th><th>Use Draft when</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Automatic creation is trusted</td><td>Catalogue users must review central content</td></tr><tr><td>Identifiers and Seller data are reliable</td><td>Records require enrichment or compliance review</td></tr><tr><td>The storefront is prepared to use new records</td><td>The Operator wants controlled activation</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Define who reviews Draft records, what information must be present, who can activate the record, the review SLA and whether Draft records can participate in matching or storefront publication.</p>\n","Manage the Golden Record Data Source":"\n<p>The <strong>source Advert</strong> is the linked Seller Advert that supplies updates to the Golden Record when Seller update propagation is enabled. The Advert that triggers Golden Record creation becomes the initial source.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Source Seller Advert changes</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Golden Record is updated</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Linked Seller records may receive central data through backfill</strong></div></div></div>\n<h3>Data source fallback</h3><p>When fallback is enabled and the source Advert is deleted, another linked Advert can become the source. Review source changes after Seller deletion or offboarding because the replacement may use different titles, images, descriptions or attributes.</p>\n<h3>Change the source manually</h3><ol><li>Go to <code>Adverts &gt; Central Product Database</code>.</li><li>Edit the Golden Product.</li><li>Open the linked-Seller controls under Golden Product Variants.</li><li>Select the intended Seller Advert.</li><li>Choose <strong>Set as data source</strong>.</li><li>Save and validate the Golden Product.</li></ol>\n<h3>Source governance</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Record the current source Seller and why it was selected</li><li>Review content quality before changing the source</li><li>Assess fallback before Seller offboarding</li><li>Assign approval for source changes</li><li>Review propagation and backfill after the change</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Correct shared content at its approved source.</strong> When the Golden Record owns a shared attribute, update the Golden Record and use the approved propagation or backfill process. Editing only the linked Seller Advert may be temporary or may be overwritten later.</div>\n","Establish Barcode and Product Identity Standards":"\n<p>Automatic Golden Record creation and linking depend primarily on Variant barcodes such as EAN, UPC and GTIN.</p>\n<p>Sellers must use the identifier for the specific sellable Variant, not a carton barcode, warehouse location code, internal reference or barcode reused across different products.</p>\n<h3>Define barcode controls</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Required format and length</li><li>Uniqueness</li><li>Leading zero handling</li><li>Spaces and special characters</li><li>Missing identifiers</li><li>Duplicate and reused identifiers</li><li>Bundles and multipacks</li><li>Products legitimately sold without a GTIN</li><li>Barcode correction after linking</li></ul>\n<h3>Strict barcode enforcement</h3><p>When strict barcode rules are enabled, every Golden Variant requires one unique barcode and barcode uniqueness is enforced across the CPD.</p>\n<h3>Correct a linked barcode</h3><ol><li>Confirm the current barcode is wrong.</li><li>Confirm the correct product identity.</li><li>Review every linked Seller offer.</li><li>Determine whether the Seller Variant must be unlinked.</li><li>Correct the Golden Variant or Seller Variant through the approved workflow.</li><li>Validate the new relationship and storefront result.</li></ol>\n<h3>SKU matching</h3><p>Use optional SKU matching only when the SKU is a standard manufacturer identifier across Sellers. Seller-specific or duplicated SKUs can create incorrect links. Barcode matching should remain the primary control where reliable barcodes are available.</p>\n","Understand Auto-Create and Auto-Link Behaviour":"\n<h3>Auto-create</h3><p>A Golden Product and Golden Variant can be created automatically when the relevant setting is enabled, the Seller Variant is valid, applicable Catalog Rules pass, Product Vetting approval has occurred where required and the barcode does not match an existing Golden Variant.</p>\n<p>Marketplacer can consider an existing Golden Product associated with the Advert, matching sibling Variants, a CPD product with matching title, Brand and Category, or creation of a new Golden Product.</p>\n<h3>Auto-link</h3><p>A Seller Variant can link automatically when auto-linking is enabled, its barcode matches an existing Golden Variant, the Product and Variant are valid, Catalog Rules pass and Product Vetting approval has occurred where required.</p>\n<h3>Common triggers</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Variant creation</li><li>Supported Variant updates</li><li>Product Vetting approval</li></ul>\n<p>Supported updates can include barcode, SKU, Option Values, tax information, Shipping Profile, parcel dimensions, recommended retail price, measurements and supported regulated-product fields.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not assume every correction behaves like initial creation.</strong> A Variant initially created without a barcode or in an invalid state may require deliberate reprocessing. Test the correction path in Sandbox.</div>\n<h3>Product Vetting interaction</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Seller creates or imports product</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Product becomes valid</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Operator approves product</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Auto-create or auto-link logic runs</strong></div></div></div>\n","Manage Multi-Variant Linking":"\n<p>Multi-Variant Adverts require additional review because one Variant's match can affect the Golden Product associated with the complete Advert.</p>\n<h3>All Variants belong to one Golden Product</h3><pre><code>Seller Advert: Running Shoe\n├── Size 7 → Golden Product A\n├── Size 8 → Golden Product A\n└── Size 9 → Golden Product A</code></pre>\n<h3>One Variant matches and siblings are new</h3><pre><code>Seller Advert\n├── Small → matches Golden Product A\n├── Medium → no existing Golden Variant\n└── Large → no existing Golden Variant</code></pre>\n<p>When auto-create is enabled, the unmatched sibling Variants can be created under the same Golden Product as the matching Variant.</p>\n<h3>Partial Seller overlap</h3><pre><code>Golden Product: Team Jersey\n\nGolden Variant: Small\n└── Seller A\n\nGolden Variant: Medium\n├── Seller A\n└── Seller B\n\nGolden Variant: Large\n└── Seller B</code></pre>\n<p>Small resolves only to Seller A and Large resolves only to Seller B because each has one linked offer. Medium has two linked Seller offers and therefore requires the Operator's buy-box or offer-selection logic.</p>\n<h3>Variants appear to match different Golden Products</h3><pre><code>Seller Advert\n├── Red → Golden Product A\n└── Blue → Golden Product B</code></pre>\n<p>Investigate whether the Seller grouped unrelated products together, a barcode is wrong, the CPD contains duplicates, a Golden Variant belongs under the wrong product or the Advert should be split.</p>\n<h3>Advert relinking</h3><p>A single-Variant Advert can move to the newly matched Golden Product. A multi-Variant Advert may remain linked to the original Golden Product depending on the other Variant relationships.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Review the complete Advert and every sibling Variant, not only the Variant that triggered the match.</strong></div>\n","Create and Manage Golden Records":"\n<p>Go to:</p><p><code>Adverts &gt; Central Product Database</code></p>\n<h3>Create a Golden Product</h3><ol><li>Select <strong>Create Golden Product</strong>.</li><li>Enter the required product information.</li><li>Submit the record.</li><li>Add the required Golden Variants.</li><li>Review status and identifiers.</li><li>Confirm the intended source and linked Seller relationships.</li></ol>\n<h3>Add a Golden Variant</h3><ol><li>Edit the Golden Product.</li><li>Go to Golden Product Variants.</li><li>Select <strong>Create New Variant</strong>.</li><li>Enter Variant information and barcode.</li><li>Save the Variant and Golden Product.</li></ol>\n<h3>Edit a Golden Record</h3><ol><li>Find and edit the Golden Product.</li><li>Update only approved fields.</li><li>Review propagation and backfill impact.</li><li>Save and allow asynchronous processing to complete.</li><li>Validate the Golden Record and linked Seller offers.</li></ol>\n<h3>Link a Seller Variant manually</h3><ol><li>Edit the correct Golden Product.</li><li>Find the intended Golden Variant.</li><li>Open the link action.</li><li>Enter the Seller Variant ID.</li><li>Confirm the identity match.</li><li>Save and validate the relationship.</li></ol>\n<p>Before manual linking, confirm the products are identical, the Golden Variant is correct, the identity evidence is reliable and backfill will not overwrite required Seller data.</p>\n","Add Seller Products Using Barcode Matching":"\n<p>Sellers can use an existing Golden Record when manually adding a product.</p><p><code>Seller Portal &gt; Products &gt; Add Products</code></p>\n<ol><li>Start the manual product-creation workflow.</li><li>Enter a Variant barcode.</li><li>Search the CPD.</li><li>Review the matched Golden Record.</li><li>Select <strong>Use this product's information</strong>.</li><li>Add any remaining Variants.</li><li>Complete Seller-specific details.</li><li>Submit the product.</li></ol>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Can come from the Golden Record</th><th>Seller still provides</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Product name, description, Brand, images, Variant attributes and identifiers</td><td>Price, Sale price, stock, shipping, Seller-specific attributes and required Seller Variant details</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>No match found</h3><p>Confirm the barcode, try another Variant barcode where appropriate, use the standard product workflow where permitted or contact the Operator when the product should exist in the CPD.</p>\n<h3>Wrong product matched</h3><p>Stop before publication and review the entered barcode, Golden Variant, linked Seller Variants, duplicate records and AI-assisted matching result.</p>\n","Search and Audit the Central Product Database":"\n<p>Use <code>Adverts &gt; Central Product Database</code> to search by Golden Product ID, name, Category, Brand, year, SKU, barcode, price range and creation or update date.</p>\n<p>Quality filters can identify records with or without associated Adverts, missing descriptions, images, specifications, dimensions, Sale type, Option Values or Golden Variant images, and records linked to more than one Seller.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Recurring queue</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Without Seller offers</td><td>Identify unused or preloaded records</td></tr><tr><td>With several Sellers</td><td>Review consolidated-offer coverage and buy-box readiness</td></tr><tr><td>Missing descriptions or images</td><td>Central content enrichment</td></tr><tr><td>Missing Option Values</td><td>Variant-structure review</td></tr><tr><td>Recently created or updated</td><td>Validate automation and source changes</td></tr><tr><td>Draft records</td><td>Complete review and activation</td></tr><tr><td>Duplicate barcode candidates</td><td>Investigate identity and merge risk</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Recommended cadence</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Daily during onboarding or migration: new Golden Records, incorrect matches and failed imports</li><li>Weekly: Drafts, missing content, multiple-Seller records, source changes and backfill exceptions</li><li>Monthly: CPD growth, unused records, content quality, Seller coverage, merges and deletions</li></ul>\n","Bulk Export and Upload Golden Records":"\n<h3>Bulk export</h3><p><code>Adverts &gt; Central Product Database &gt; Manage Data &gt; Bulk export</code></p>\n<p>Filter the CPD before export. Generated files are delivered as XLSX. Large result sets should be divided with filters so the export remains within the supported row limit.</p>\n<h3>Bulk upload</h3><p><code>Adverts &gt; Central Product Database &gt; Manage Data &gt; Bulk upload</code></p>\n<p>Use bulk upload to create or update Golden Products and Golden Variants, enrich central content and correct data at scale.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Filter and export CPD records</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Retain an untouched raw export</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Update a controlled working copy</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Upload and review results</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Validate representative records</strong></div></div></div>\n<h3>Protect identifiers</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Golden Product ID</li><li>Golden Variant ID</li><li>Barcode</li><li>Category and Brand IDs</li><li>Option Values</li><li>Source and linkage information where available</li></ul>\n<p>Test a small sample first, preserve leading zeros in barcodes, distinguish create from update actions and confirm no unintended duplicates were created.</p>\n","Load Products into a Seller Account":"\n<p>The Operator can create linked Seller products from selected CPD records.</p>\n<ol><li>Go to <code>Adverts &gt; Central Product Database</code>.</li><li>Filter the required Golden Products.</li><li>Select <code>Manage Data &gt; Load products on seller</code>.</li><li>Select the Seller.</li><li>Confirm the action.</li></ol>\n<p>Products can be loaded to one Seller at a time through this action. The created Seller products and Variants are linked to the Golden Records and can receive backfill where enabled.</p>\n<h3>Use this for</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Seller onboarding</li><li>Pre-approved assortment</li><li>Centrally curated ranges</li><li>Products already represented in the CPD</li><li>Reducing Seller product-entry effort</li></ul>\n<h3>The Seller may still need to complete</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Price and stock</li><li>Shipping</li><li>Seller SKU</li><li>Seller-specific attributes</li><li>Product validation and Product Vetting</li><li>Publication</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Loading a CPD product into a Seller account does not automatically make it purchasable.</strong></div>\n","Configure Backfill and Autopublish":"\n<p>Backfill applies supported Golden Record content to linked Seller Adverts and Variants. It operates according to each Seller's ProductDB policy and separately from the act of linking.</p>\n<p>Go to:</p><p><code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller &gt; ProductDB</code></p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Policy</th><th>Behaviour</th><th>Use when</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Never</td><td>Regular CPD backfill does not update the Seller product</td><td>The Seller or connected platform remains the content source</td></tr><tr><td>Only If Missing</td><td>Supported empty fields are populated from the Golden Record</td><td>Central data should enrich without replacing existing values</td></tr><tr><td>Always</td><td>Supported Seller fields are replaced by Golden Record content</td><td>The CPD is the approved shared-content source</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Always can overwrite Seller content.</strong> Review source ownership and integration behaviour before enabling it.</div>\n<h3>Manual backfill</h3><ol><li>Confirm the Seller backfill policy.</li><li>Edit the Golden Product.</li><li>Complete the approved central updates.</li><li>Select <strong>Backfill advert</strong>.</li><li>Choose whether to include new or updated Golden Variants.</li><li>Allow asynchronous processing to complete.</li><li>Validate the linked Seller Advert.</li></ol>\n<h3>Autopublish</h3><p>Backfill can publish Seller Adverts automatically after central content makes them valid. Test required Seller fields, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting, stock, price, shipping and storefront ingestion before using autopublish.</p>\n","Use Golden Records with MConnect":"\n<p>MConnect can match newly imported Seller products to Golden Records.</p>\n<h3>Review these MConnect settings</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><strong>Use information from the product database to create Variants and products if a barcode match is found</strong></li><li><strong>Allow matching items against the product database via the SKU field</strong></li></ul>\n<h3>Barcode matching flow</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>MConnect imports a Seller Variant</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Barcode is checked against the CPD</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Seller Variant links to the Golden Variant</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Missing supported information is filled</strong></div></div></div>\n<h3>MConnect backfill exception</h3><p>When MConnect creates a product and finds a matching Golden Record, missing supported fields can be filled from the CPD even when the Seller's regular backfill policy is <strong>Never</strong>. Explain and test this during Seller onboarding.</p>\n<h3>SKU matching risk</h3><p>Enable SKU matching only when SKUs are standardised across Sellers and duplicate risk is controlled. Seller-specific SKUs can cause incorrect links.</p>\n<h3>Confirm source ownership</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Which attributes remain sourced from Shopify or the connected platform</li><li>Which attributes are supplied by the CPD</li><li>Which fields can be overwritten</li><li>How later Seller and Golden Record updates behave</li><li>Whether manual Marketplacer edits will be overwritten</li></ul>\n","Review AI-Assisted CPD Matching":"\n<p>AI-assisted CPD matching helps identify cases where a Seller Variant's barcode matches a Golden Variant but the accompanying information appears to describe a different product.</p>\n<p>The comparison can consider title, description, Brand, images, Variant information and Option Types or Values.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Verdict</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Same</td><td>The Seller product appears consistent with the Golden Record</td></tr><tr><td>Different</td><td>A potential mismatch exists</td></tr><tr><td>Processing</td><td>The comparison has not completed</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Respond to Same</h3><p>Continue normal barcode, Product, Variant, Catalog Rule and Product Vetting checks.</p>\n<h3>Respond to Different</h3><ol><li>Review Seller and Golden Variant barcodes.</li><li>Compare title, description, Brand, images and Option Values.</li><li>Review sibling Variants and linked Seller offers.</li><li>Correct the Seller data, barcode or Golden Record as appropriate.</li><li>Reject or prevent linking when identity remains uncertain.</li></ol>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>The AI verdict is advisory.</strong> It does not replace barcode governance, Seller evidence, catalogue review or Operator judgement.</div>\n","Manage Duplicates and Merges":"\n<p>Duplicate Golden Records can result from missing or incorrect barcodes, inconsistent product grouping, separate manual creation, simultaneous imports or older records created before matching controls were available.</p>\n<h3>Automatic merge</h3><p>When automatic merging is enabled, Golden Products sharing a Golden Variant barcode can merge during supported matching flows such as UI creation, spreadsheet import, MConnect, API or Product Vetting.</p>\n<h3>Manual merge</h3><p><code>Adverts &gt; Central Product Database &gt; Manage Data &gt; Merge products</code></p>\n<ol><li>Select two Golden Products.</li><li>Review the merge preview.</li><li>Confirm the surviving record.</li><li>Verify linked Variants and Seller Adverts.</li><li>Confirm the merge.</li></ol>\n<h3>Which record survives</h3><ol><li>The Golden Product with the most linked Variants is retained.</li><li>If both have the same number, the older Golden Product is retained.</li></ol>\n<p>The Operator cannot choose another surviving record. Seller Adverts and Variants move to the retained record, but content from the deleted record is not combined or reconciled.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Improve the record that will survive before merging.</strong> Marketplacer does not combine the best content from both records.</div>\n<h3>Controls</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Confirm both records represent the same product</li><li>Compare every Golden Variant, barcode and Option Value</li><li>Export both records</li><li>Review linked Sellers and storefront impact</li><li>Obtain approval</li><li>Review the Activity Log after merging</li></ul>\n<p>Manual merges are limited to two records at a time, merging is permanent and automatic merges may not generate an Operator notification.</p>\n","Delete and Recreate Golden Records":"\n<p>Golden Record deletion is permanent. There is no soft delete, restore or undo.</p>\n<p>Deleting a Golden Record removes it from the CPD but does not automatically delete linked Seller Adverts.</p>\n<h3>Deletion process</h3><ol><li>Apply precise CPD filters.</li><li>Export the affected records.</li><li>Confirm every result is intended for deletion.</li><li>Select <code>Manage Data &gt; Delete Results</code>.</li><li>Complete the approval process.</li><li>Confirm deletion.</li><li>Validate linked Seller Adverts, integrations and storefront behaviour.</li></ol>\n<h3>Recreation</h3><p>A deleted Golden Record can be recreated when eligible Seller Variants remain and supported update or Product Vetting triggers run. Recreation produces new Golden Product and Golden Variant IDs, a newly selected source Seller and new linking relationships.</p>\n<p>Previously linked Sellers may need to update their Variants to relink.</p>\n<h3>Before deletion</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Record Golden Product and Variant IDs</li><li>Record linked Sellers and Seller Variant IDs</li><li>Record the current data source</li><li>Review storefront URLs and external references</li><li>Confirm deletion is preferable to correction or merging</li><li>Define the recreation and validation plan</li></ul>\n","Troubleshoot Golden Record Issues":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Issue</th><th>Review</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller Variant did not auto-link</td><td>Auto-link setting, barcode format, validity, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting, AI result and existing links</td></tr><tr><td>New Golden Record was not created</td><td>Auto-create setting, initial barcode, validity, matching records, title, Brand, Category and supported trigger</td></tr><tr><td>Linked product was not backfilled</td><td>Seller policy, MConnect creation exception, supported field, asynchronous processing and manual backfill</td></tr><tr><td>Seller content was overwritten</td><td>Always policy, MConnect creation, source propagation, manual backfill and connected source sync</td></tr><tr><td>Golden Record changed unexpectedly</td><td>Propagation, current source, fallback, source deletion, bulk upload, API update and Activity Logs</td></tr><tr><td>Advert moved to another Golden Product</td><td>Barcode changes, sibling links, Product Vetting, auto-link and automatic merge</td></tr><tr><td>Wrong Seller product matched</td><td>Barcode reuse, Golden Variant identity, AI verdict, images, description and manual-link history</td></tr><tr><td>Golden Record disappeared</td><td>Deletion, automatic merge, surviving record and Activity Logs</td></tr><tr><td>Record was recreated with different IDs</td><td>Expected result after deletion and recreation; update references and links</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Stop publication when product identity is uncertain.</strong> Resolve the barcode and product relationship before allowing the offer to reach customers.</div>\n","Golden Record Permissions and Change Control":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Permission area</th><th>Typical access</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Manage Golden Records (CPD)</td><td>View, create, update and delete Golden Products and Variants, link Seller Variants, load CPD products and trigger backfill</td></tr><tr><td>Manage Golden Records backfill settings</td><td>View and edit Seller CPD policies</td></tr><tr><td>Manage product catalogue</td><td>Search, import, export and manage Product Vetting</td></tr><tr><td>View imports and exports</td><td>Review bulk processing results</td></tr><tr><td>View Activity Logs</td><td>Review user and system changes</td></tr><tr><td>Manage marketplace configuration</td><td>Access relevant Golden Product Settings</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Apply separation of duties</h3><p>Consider separating CPD quality review, bulk upload, source changes, backfill settings, merge approval, deletion approval and Production configuration.</p>\n<h3>High-risk actions</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Enable automatic merging</li><li>Change the source Seller</li><li>Set backfill to Always</li><li>Bulk-load products into a Seller account</li><li>Bulk-upload CPD records</li><li>Merge or delete Golden Products</li><li>Change Production auto-create and auto-link settings</li></ul>\n<p>Retain the request, reason, affected records, before and after state, approver, validation result and recovery plan.</p>\n","Test Golden Records End to End":"\n<h3>Configuration</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Auto-create on and off</li><li>Active and Draft creation</li><li>Auto-link on and off</li><li>Strict barcode enforcement</li><li>Propagation and source fallback</li><li>Barcode update restriction</li><li>Automatic merging</li></ul>\n<h3>Creation and matching</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Unique, existing, missing, invalid and duplicate barcodes</li><li>Product initially invalid and later corrected</li><li>Product Vetting approval and Catalog Rule failure</li><li>Seller Portal barcode search, correct match, no match and wrong match</li><li>AI verdicts Same, Different and Processing</li></ul>\n<h3>Multi-Variant and buy-box</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>All Variants match one Golden Product</li><li>One Variant matches and siblings are new</li><li>Two Sellers partially overlap in Variant coverage</li><li>Several Seller offers link to one Golden Variant</li><li>Hidden and overt buy-box behaviour</li><li>Preferred offer becomes out of stock</li></ul>\n<h3>Backfill and integrations</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Never, Only If Missing and Always</li><li>Manual backfill and autopublish</li><li>MConnect barcode and SKU matching</li><li>MConnect backfill while the regular policy is Never</li><li>Later Seller and Golden Record updates</li></ul>\n<h3>Operations</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Search and quality filters</li><li>Bulk export and controlled upload</li><li>Load products into one Seller</li><li>Manual merge and correct surviving record</li><li>Deletion and recreation with new IDs</li><li>Activity Log review</li></ul>\n","Operator Readiness Checklist":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>The consolidated-product customer experience is approved</li><li>Golden Records are appropriate for the catalogue</li><li>Golden Product and Seller-offer ownership are documented</li><li>Barcode and identity standards are defined</li><li>Products without reliable identifiers have a separate process</li><li>Every Golden Product Setting has been reviewed</li><li>Active versus Draft creation is intentional</li><li>Auto-create and auto-link are tested</li><li>Product Vetting and Catalog Rule interaction is understood</li><li>Multi-Variant linking and partial Seller overlap are tested</li><li>Buy-box ranking is implemented in the frontend or orchestration layer</li><li>Source propagation and fallback are intentional</li><li>Source changes have an approval process</li><li>Barcode restrictions have a correction process</li><li>Seller backfill policies are documented</li><li>MConnect's creation-time backfill behaviour is understood</li><li>Seller barcode matching and AI-assisted matching are tested</li><li>CPD quality queues have owners</li><li>Bulk export, upload and load-to-Seller actions are controlled</li><li>Merges and deletions require evidence and approval</li><li>Recreated-record ID changes are understood</li><li>Permissions follow least privilege</li><li>Seller, Operator, integration and storefront behaviour is tested end to end</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/24732565327885-Central-Product-Database-Golden-Records\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Central Product Database: Golden Records</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/34974601996301-Golden-Product-settings-configuration\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Golden Product Settings Configuration</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/24733705437197-Manage-Golden-Products-in-Operator-portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Golden Products in the Operator Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/37154382517517-Golden-Record-auto-create-and-auto-link-triggers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Golden Record Auto-Create and Auto-Link Triggers</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/37154427683597-Golden-Record-linking-behaviour\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Golden Record Linking Behaviour</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/37154546531341-Understanding-the-source-for-a-Golden-Record\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Understanding the Source for a Golden Record</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/24734837065613-Backfill-and-Autopublish\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Backfill and Autopublish</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/24734785464845-Golden-Records-and-MConnect\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Golden Records and MConnect</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/43394441058829-Add-products-using-barcodes-and-Golden-Record-matching\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Add Products Using Barcodes and Golden Record Matching</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/43095819522573-AI-assisted-CPD-matching-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">AI-Assisted CPD Matching Overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/38119329496717-Golden-record-search-filters\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Golden Record Search Filters</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/38123753865613-Bulk-export-and-upload-products-via-Central-Product-Database-page\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bulk Export and Upload through the CPD</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/37769344967437-Load-products-to-a-seller-account\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Load Products to a Seller Account</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39929717996045-Manually-merge-Golden-Records-using-the-Central-Product-Database-UI\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manually Merge Golden Records</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39929785340941-Auto-merge-Golden-Records-based-on-barcodes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Auto-Merge Golden Records Based on Barcodes</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/37154499143565-Delete-or-recreate-a-Golden-Record\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Delete or Recreate a Golden Record</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator User Role Permissions</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["product-model","Product Model"],["product-source-of-truth","Product Source of Truth"],["mconnect","MConnect"],["product-vetting","Product Vetting"],["catalogue-quality","Catalogue Quality Operations"]]},"catalogue-quality":{"summary":"Maintain catalogue quality after launch by defining measurable standards, building operational queues, correcting the right source, enriching products safely and turning repeated issues into prevention.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller onboarding","Category and ecommerce teams","Compliance and integration owners"],"sections":{"Understanding Catalogue Quality Operations":"\n<p>Catalogue quality continues after Seller onboarding because Sellers add and change products, Variants, images, prices, stock, Categories and shipping throughout their lifecycle.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Define standards</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Detect and prioritise issues</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Assign the correct owner</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Correct the source of truth</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Validate and prevent recurrence</strong></div></div></div>\n<p>Quality includes completeness, accuracy, consistency, structure, discoverability, presentation, fulfilment readiness, commercial readiness and compliance.</p>\n","Define the Marketplace Product Standard":"\n<p>Document the minimum Advert and Variant information required for publication, then separate required data from preferred enrichment.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Level</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Required</td><td>Price greater than zero</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplace standard</td><td>Description above an agreed length</td></tr><tr><td>Enrichment opportunity</td><td>Additional lifestyle images</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>For wholesale, every applicable Variant must be marked as wholesale and contain a positive Wholesale Price. Convert measurable standards into Catalog Rules and reserve judgement-based standards for human review.</p>\n","Build Operational Quality Queues":"\n<p>Use <code>Adverts &gt; Search Adverts</code> to create focused queues by Seller, Category, status, date, Advert ID, Variant ID, SKU or barcode.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Requires Vetting</li><li>Failed Catalog Rules</li><li>Previously Rejected</li><li>Recently Created or Updated</li><li>Out of Stock or unavailable</li><li>Category review</li><li>Seller quality review</li></ul>\n<p>Export invalid products where a controlled spreadsheet review is useful. Use the smallest practical queue so Sellers and catalogue teams change only affected records.</p>\n","Investigate Errors, Changes and Duplicates":"\n<p>Review Seller Portal product errors, Product Vetting rejection reasons, Recently updated changes, duplicate-barcode warnings, Activity Logs, MConnect Items and Audit Logs, and Imports &amp; Exports.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Identify the cause before correcting.</strong> The issue may originate in Seller data, an integration transformation, Mapping, Marketplacer configuration or the storefront.</div>\n<p>A completed spreadsheet task can still contain failed rows. Review expected, processed and failed counts, then validate representative Adverts and Variants.</p>\n","Plan and Complete Product Enrichment":"\n<p>Enrichment can improve titles, descriptions, images, attributes, accessibility text and Variant information beyond the minimum valid product.</p>\n<p>Complete enrichment in the approved source of truth. For an MConnect Seller, update the Seller platform for fields that remain synchronised. Use Marketplacer for marketplace-specific fields or fields deliberately removed from sync. Use the Operator ecommerce platform for front-end-only SEO, Collections and merchandising content.</p>\n<p>AI-generated descriptions should be treated as drafts and reviewed for accuracy, unsupported claims, measurements, ingredients, safety and regulatory wording.</p>\n","Correct Products at the Right Source and in Bulk":"\n<p>Choose the correction path according to field ownership and product volume.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Situation</th><th>Method</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Small Marketplacer-owned correction</td><td>Seller Portal</td></tr><tr><td>Several products for one spreadsheet Seller</td><td>Bulk Product Management</td></tr><tr><td>Cross-Seller controlled correction</td><td>Search Adverts export and approved bulk import</td></tr><tr><td>Source value problem</td><td>MConnect, API, XML or Seller source</td></tr><tr><td>Mapping issue</td><td>Mapping workspace</td></tr><tr><td>Central product issue</td><td>Central Product Database</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>After correction, confirm Catalog Rules, Mapping, Product Vetting, price, stock, Shipping Profile, wholesale status and storefront presentation.</p>\n","Measure Catalogue Health and Seller Quality":"\n<p>Track marketplace, Seller and Category measures such as valid product percentage, Catalog Rule failures, first-pass vetting approval, Mapping backlog, missing images, missing Shipping Profiles, wholesale errors, failed imports and MConnect errors.</p>\n<p>Use representative sampling alongside automated measures. Review top-selling products, newly imported products, trusted Sellers without vetting, high-risk Categories and customer-facing search results.</p>\n<p>Compare the Seller source, integration result, Marketplacer Advert and Variants, ecommerce platform and customer-facing page to locate where quality degrades.</p>\n","Govern Continuous Catalogue Improvement":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Cadence</th><th>Focus</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Daily</td><td>Failed imports, urgent vetting, products unexpectedly offline and critical price or stock issues</td></tr><tr><td>Weekly</td><td>Catalog Rule failures, Mapping, rejected products, recently updated products and wholesale errors</td></tr><tr><td>Monthly</td><td>Seller and Category quality trends, enrichment and repeated causes</td></tr><tr><td>Quarterly</td><td>Standards, rules, vetting approach, ownership and Seller support model</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Turn repeated issues into better Catalog Rules, Mapping, source validation, Seller training, workbook guidance or performance management.</p>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39514847581709-Search-Adverts-in-the-Operator-portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Search Adverts in the Operator Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8139439502989-Review-and-fix-product-errors-as-a-seller\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Review and Fix Product Errors as a Seller</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/18648438735373-Identify-duplicate-products\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Identify Duplicate Products</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360055991052-Activity-Logs-in-Marketplacer-operator-admin\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Activity Logs in Marketplacer Operator Admin</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/10607256918925-Imports-and-exports-using-spreadsheets\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Imports and Exports Using Spreadsheets</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/30216341608333-Generate-product-descriptions-using-AI\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Generate Product Descriptions Using AI</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["product-source-of-truth","Product Source of Truth"],["product-vetting","Product Vetting"],["catalog-rules","Catalog Rules"],["golden-records","Golden Records and Central Product Database"],["seller-performance","Seller Performance"]]}};
